// Graph Utilities
// Parses Kodex topic relationships and generates Mermaid graph syntax from them.

FUNCTION parseRelatedTopics(relatedText) -> string[]                    EXPORT
  Extract all backtick-wrapped topic slugs (pattern: `topic-name`) from the text.
  Return a deduplicated array of topic names.

---

FUNCTION buildGraphEdges(topics) -> GraphEdge[]                         EXPORT
  CALLS: parseRelatedTopics (graph-utils)
  For each topic that has a related field, parse related topics and create a GraphEdge
  { source: topic.name, target: relatedTopicName } for each referenced topic.
  Return the full array of edges.

---

FUNCTION generateMermaidGraph(edges, topics) -> string                  EXPORT
  Build a left-to-right Mermaid flowchart (graph LR).
  Collect the set of node names that appear in edges.
  Define each node as: name["Title"] using the topic's title (or name if no title).
  Define each edge as: source --> target.
  Return the complete Mermaid source as a string.
